### ============================================================
### US-PROPERTY-01 / US-PROPERTY-02 — Property create, list, view, update
### (Landlord only; ownership enforced — cross-landlord fetch → 404)
### ------------------------------------------------------------
### Run in the "local" (or "device") environment from
### rest-client.env.json. The login block below captures
### @accessToken / @refreshToken for every request that follows.
### ============================================================
### ============================================================
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### capture tokens
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### ============================================================
### US-PROPERTY-01 — Create a property
### Expect 201 { data: { id, name, address, landlordId, ... } }
### Validation: name + address required (unique per landlord).
### ============================================================
# @name createProperty
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sunshine Apartments",
  "address": "123 Le Loi, District 1, HCMC"
}

###
@propertyId = {{createProperty.response.body.data.id}}

###

### Create with missing fields (expect 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}

###

### Create duplicate name for same landlord (expect 409 CONFLICT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sunshine Apartments",
  "address": "456 Nguyen Hue, District 1, HCMC"
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-PROPERTY-02 — List owned properties
### Expect 200 paginated { data:[...], meta:{...} }
### ============================================================
# @name listProperties
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-PROPERTY-02 — View a single owned property
### Expect 200 { data: { id, name, address, ... } }
### ============================================================
# @name getProperty
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### ============================================================
### US-PROPERTY-02 — Update property details
### Expect 200 with updated values. Invalid update rejected
### without changing the stored row.
### ============================================================
# @name updateProperty
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sunshine Apartments (Renamed)",
  "address": "789 Dong Khoi, District 1, HCMC"
}

###

### Update with empty name (expect 400 VALIDATION_ERROR)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}

###

### ============================================================
### US-AUTH-04 — Cross-ownership: a property owned by another
### landlord is not visible. Replace {{otherLandlordPropertyId}}
### with an id owned by a different landlord to expect 404.
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties/{{otherLandlordPropertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Unauthenticated request (expect 401 UNAUTHENTICATED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/properties

###
